        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 4:59PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 459 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
north of Ratcliff, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Jethro...                         Charleston...
Cass...                           Red Star...
Branch...                         Turners Bend...
Vesta...                          Cecil...
Lonelm...                         Boston...
Dutton...                         Altus...
Denning...                        Etna...
Alix...                           Barnes...
Pettigrew...                      St. Paul...
Redding...                        Watalula...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 23 and
42.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for west central
Arkansas.</instruction>
